### GET request to example server
GET https://examples.http-client.intellij.net/get
    ?generated-in=IntelliJ IDEA

### 1. Ingest a Mock Draft Transaction into Kafka
POST http://localhost:8080/api/test/kafka/publish
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionDate": "2026-06-20",
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "category": "Food & Dining",
  "amount": 2450.00,
  "person": "Social Restaurant",
  "splits": [
    { "person": "Self", "amount": 1225.00 },
    { "person": "Sameer", "amount": 1225.00 }
  ],
  "mediaUrl": "https://example.com/receipt.png",
  "mediaType": "IMAGE",
  "rawOcrOrTranscript": "Dinner split 50/50 with Sameer"
}

###

### 2. Fetch Active Reviews in the Queue
GET http://localhost:8080/api/reviews

###

### 3. Update Review Fields Manually
# Replace {id} with the UUID of the review from the previous GET request
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/reviews/{id}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionDate": "2026-06-20",
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "category": "Food & Dining",
  "amount": 2500.00,
  "person": "Social Restaurant (Adjusted)",
  "splits": [
    { "person": "Self", "amount": 1250.00 },
    { "person": "Sameer", "amount": 1250.00 }
  ]
}

###

### 4. Approve Draft & Commit to Ledger
# Replace {id} with the UUID of the review
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reviews/{id}/approve

###

### 5. Reject & Discard Draft
# Replace {id} with the UUID of the review
POST http://localhost:8080/api/reviews/{id}/reject

###

